{"title_page": "Gerdkuh", "text_new": "{{for|the village in Gilan Province, Iran|Gerdkuh, Siahkal}}{{Infobox building\n| name = Gerdkuh\n| structural_system = \n| completion_date = \n| coordinates = \n| location_country = {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Iran]]\n| location_town = [[Damghan]]\n| address = \n| location = \n| landlord = \n| current_tenants = \n| owner = \n| client = \n| ren_cost = \n| cost = \n| architectural_style = [[Iranian architecture]]\n| native_name = \u06af\u0631\u062f\u06a9\u0648\u0647\n| building_type = Castle\n| altitude = \n| map_caption = \n| map_alt = \n| map_type = \n| caption = \n| image_size = 250\n| image_alt = \n| image = Gerd2.JPG\n| status = \n| alternate_names = \n| former_names = \n| native_name_lang = fa <!-- ISO 639-2 code -->\n| destruction_date = \n}}[[File:Si\u00e8ge de Girdk\u00fbh.jpeg|thumb|Mongolian siege of Gerdkuh. [[Hayton of Corycus]], ''Fleur des histoires d'orient.'']]\n'''Gerdk\u016bh''' or '''Girdk\u016bh''' ({{lang-fa|\u06af\u0631\u062f\u06a9\u0648\u0647}}, also known as {{lang|fa|\u062f\u0698 \u06af\u0646\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0646}} ''Dezh-e Gonbad\u0101n'', \"fortress of the domes\")<ref>[http://www.tarikhaneh.com/chehreha/damghan/gerd%20koh.htm \u0642\u0644\u0639\u0647 \u06af\u0631\u062f\u06a9\u0648\u0647 \u062f\u0627\u0645\u063a\u0627\u0646] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100406035115/http://www.tarikhaneh.com/chehreha/damghan/gerd%20koh.htm |date=2010-04-06 }} (in Persian). Retrieved 2012-04-30.</ref> was a major castle of the [[Nizari Ismaili state|Nizari Isma'ili state]] located near [[Damghan]], Iran. The castle was taken in 1096 for use by the [[Order of Assassins|Assassins]].  Due to circular shape of mountain peak, it was named ''Gerdkuh'', ''Gerd'' ({{lang|fa|[[wikt:\u06af\u0631\u062f#Persian|\u06af\u0631\u062f]]}}) for \"circular\" (round) and ''kuh'' ({{lang|fa|[[wikt:\u06a9\u0648\u0647#Persian|\u06a9\u0648\u0647]]}}) for \"mountain\". The castle was surrounded by a triple ring of forts making its position seemingly impregnable. [[Hasan Sabbah|Hassan-i Sabbah]] and other Nizari leaders often sent their families to this castle for refuge. [[Hulagu Khan]] with 5,000 men started a siege against Girdkuh in 1253. Girdkuh held out against the [[Mongol conquest of Khwarezmia|Mongol invasion of Persia]] for 17 years, and was the last [[Nizari]] stronghold in Persia to surrender to Mongols.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fortress of Girdkuh|url=http://www.iis.ac.uk/view_article.asp?ContentID=105083|publisher=[[Institute of Ismaili Studies]]|accessdate=11 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe fortress probably dates back to the pre-Islamic period. Gerdkuh was situated on the [[Khorasan Road]] and guarded the routes toward the [[Alborz mountain range]]. It was refortified and transferred into the [[Nizari Ismaili state|Nizari Ismaili]] possession in 1100 by [[Ra'is]] Mu'ayyad al-Din Muzaffar ibn Ahmad Mustawfi ({{lang|fa|\u0631\u0626\u06cc\u0633 \u0645\u0624\u06cc\u062f \u0627\u0644\u062f\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u0638\u0641\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0645\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0641\u06cc}}), a secret Ismaili convert and lieutenant of the Seljuq ''[[amir]]'' Amirdad Habashi ({{lang|fa|\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062f\u0627\u062f \u062d\u0628\u0634\u06cc}}), who in turn had acquired Gerkuh in 1096 from Sultan [[Barkiaruq]]. Now under [[Hassan-i Sabbah]], Ra'is Muzaffar continued as the commandant of the stronghold for a long time until being succeeded by his son Sharaf al-Din Muhammad.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daftary |first1=Farhad |title=GERDK\u016aH \u2013 Encyclopaedia Iranica |url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/gerdkuh |website=www.iranicaonline.org |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commonscat|Gerdkuh}}\n{{coord|36|09|43|N|54|09|25|E|region:IR_type:landmark_source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=title}}\n{{Ismaili castles}}\n{{Castles in Iran}}\n[[Category:Castles in Iran]]\n[[Category:Forts in Iran]]\n[[Category:Ismaili castles]]\n[[Category:Qumis (region)]]\n[[Category:Sieges involving the Mongol Empire]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the village in Gilan Province, Iran|Gerdkuh, Siahkal}}{{Infobox building\n| name = Gerdkuh\n| structural_system = \n| completion_date = \n| coordinates = \n| location_country = {{flagicon|Iran}} [[Iran]]\n| location_town = [[Damghan]]\n| address = \n| location = \n| landlord = \n| current_tenants = \n| owner = \n| client = \n| ren_cost = \n| cost = \n| architectural_style = [[Iranian architecture]]\n| native_name = \u06af\u0631\u062f\u06a9\u0648\u0647\n| building_type = Castle\n| altitude = \n| map_caption = \n| map_alt = \n| map_type = \n| caption = \n| image_size = 250\n| image_alt = \n| image = Gerd2.JPG\n| status = \n| alternate_names = \n| former_names = \n| native_name_lang = fa <!-- ISO 639-2 code -->\n| destruction_date = \n}}[[File:Si\u00e8ge de Girdk\u00fbh.jpeg|thumb|Mongolian siege of Gerdkuh. [[Hayton of Corycus]], ''Fleur des histoires d'orient.'']]\n'''Gerdk\u016bh''' or '''Girdk\u016bh''' ({{lang-fa|\u06af\u0631\u062f\u06a9\u0648\u0647}}, also known as {{lang|fa|\u062f\u0698 \u06af\u0646\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0646}} ''Dezh-e Gonbad\u0101n'', \"fortress of the domes\")<ref>[http://www.tarikhaneh.com/chehreha/damghan/gerd%20koh.htm \u0642\u0644\u0639\u0647 \u06af\u0631\u062f\u06a9\u0648\u0647 \u062f\u0627\u0645\u063a\u0627\u0646] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100406035115/http://www.tarikhaneh.com/chehreha/damghan/gerd%20koh.htm |date=2010-04-06 }} (in Persian). Retrieved 2012-04-30.</ref> was a major castle of the [[Nizari Ismaili state|Nizari Isma'ili state]] located near [[Damghan]], Iran. The castle was taken in 1096 for use by the [[Order of Assassins|Assassins]].  Due to circular shape of mountain peak, it was named ''Gerdkuh'', ''Gerd'' ({{lang|fa|[[wikt:\u06af\u0631\u062f#Persian|\u06af\u0631\u062f]]}}) for \"circular\" (round) and ''kuh'' ({{lang|fa|[[wikt:\u06a9\u0648\u0647#Persian|\u06a9\u0648\u0647]]}}) for \"mountain\". The castle was surrounded by a triple ring of forts making its position seemingly impregnable. [[Hasan Sabbah|Hassan-i Sabbah]] and other Nizari leaders often sent their families to this castle for refuge. [[Hulagu Khan]] with 5,000 men started a siege against Girdkuh in 1253. Girdkuh held out against the [[Mongol conquest of Khwarezmia|Mongol invasion of Persia]] for 17 years, and was the last [[Nizari]] stronghold in Persia to surrender to Mongols.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fortress of Girdkuh|url=http://www.iis.ac.uk/view_article.asp?ContentID=105083|publisher=[[Institute of Ismaili Studies]]|accessdate=11 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe fortress probably dates back to the pre-Islamic period. Gerdkuh was situated on the [[Khorasan Road]] and guarded the routes toward the [[Alborz mountain range]]. It was refortified and transferred into the [[Nizari Ismaili state|Nizari Ismaili]] possession in 1100 by [[Ra'is]] Mu'ayyad al-Din Muzaffar ibn A\u1e25mad Mustawfi ({{lang|fa|\u0631\u0626\u06cc\u0633 \u0645\u0624\u06cc\u062f \u0627\u0644\u062f\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u0638\u0641\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0645\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0641\u06cc}}), a secret Ismaili convert and lieutenant of the Seljuq ''[[amir]]'' Amirdad Habashi ({{lang|fa|\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062f\u0627\u062f \u062d\u0628\u0634\u06cc}}), who in turn had acquired Gerkuh in 1096 from Sultan [[Barkiaruq]]. Now under [[Hassan-i Sabbah]], Ra'is Muzaffar continued as the commandant of the stronghold for a long time until being succeeded by his son Sharaf al-Din Muhammad.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daftary |first1=Farhad |title=GERDK\u016aH \u2013 Encyclopaedia Iranica |url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/gerdkuh |website=www.iranicaonline.org |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commonscat|Gerdkuh}}\n{{coord|36|09|43|N|54|09|25|E|region:IR_type:landmark_source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=title}}\n{{Ismaili castles}}\n{{Castles in Iran}}\n[[Category:Castles in Iran]]\n[[Category:Forts in Iran